WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:05.041 --> 00:02:07.209
These are our terms.

3
00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:10.922
One hundred of your golden dragons.

4
00:02:10.923 --> 00:02:12.340
Per ship?

5
00:02:13.758 --> 00:02:15.050
Per man.

6
00:02:15.051 --> 00:02:18.263
I could not produce such a coin.
even if I wanted to.

7
00:02:18.264 --> 00:02:20.055
Again. you plead poverty.

8
00:02:20.056 --> 00:02:22.933
It is hollow stuff
from the mouth of a Lannister.

9
00:02:22.934 --> 00:02:26.563
Whose very stables and sculleries
are carved into a mountain of gold.

10
00:02:26.564 --> 00:02:29.378
And we will need it
before this war is done.

11
00:02:29.379 --> 00:02:32.192
Break the blockade
and it will benefit you.

12
00:02:32.193 --> 00:02:36.740
Do you think that we lack for buyers
for our tapestries and perfumes?

13
00:02:36.741 --> 00:02:40.285
We sell where we please. blockade or no.

14
00:02:41.036 --> 00:02:43.787
Essos is as rich as it is vast.

15
00:02:43.788 --> 00:02:48.084
It seems you need us
more than we need you.

16
00:02:51.963 --> 00:02:53.131
The Stepstones.

17
00:02:56.509 --> 00:02:57.510
What of them?

18
00:02:58.011 --> 00:02:59.512
Give us the Stepstones.

19
00:03:00.764 --> 00:03:02.349
A smattering of rocks.

20
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:06.603
Hardly a sacrifice
to the lords of Westeros.

21
00:03:08.146 --> 00:03:11.816
Those rocks have been
disputed for a generation.

22
00:03:13.109 --> 00:03:14.319
Your...

23
00:03:15.236 --> 00:03:19.239
pirates have waylaid ships.
taken slaves. cargo...

24
00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:24.496
Give them to us outright. if you prevail.
and all that will cease.

25
00:03:24.497 --> 00:03:27.957
We will impose a simple tax
on those passing through.

26
00:03:27.958 --> 00:03:29.959
Recoup the losses we took fighting

27
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:31.960
- the Velaryon hordes.
- Extortion.

28
00:03:31.961 --> 00:03:33.922
You will drive up
the price of basic goods.

29
00:03:33.923 --> 00:03:37.258
It is better than starving. surely.

30
00:03:41.012 --> 00:03:44.431
A fleet of warships. then.
sailing at your command.

31
00:03:44.432 --> 00:03:47.852
They would break the blockade
and hold the passage.

32
00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:54.818
Very well.

33
00:03:58.655 --> 00:04:01.407
The prince regent
may have me hanged for this.

34
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:05.829
With the armada we send now.
you can topple the prince regent

35
00:04:05.830 --> 00:04:07.956
and sit the Iron Throne yourself.

36
00:04:12.836 --> 00:04:16.756
Of course. there is one more condition.

37
00:04:19.384 --> 00:04:20.635
I was...

38
00:04:21.136 --> 00:04:23.220
rather set on a bath and a flagon of wine.

39
00:04:23.221 --> 00:04:26.161
The commander of our fleet
must agree to go with you.

40
00:04:26.162 --> 00:04:29.102
His name is Lohar.
The sailors are fiercely loyal to him.

41
00:04:29.103 --> 00:04:32.230
If he does not lead them.
they will not fight.

42
00:04:34.816 --> 00:04:36.026
Very well.

43
00:04:36.735 --> 00:04:39.362
Let us meet this commander then.

44
00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:51.666
Admiral Lohar.

45
00:04:52.876 --> 00:04:57.005
this is Tyland Lannister.
of Casterly Rock.

46
00:04:57.964 --> 00:05:00.383
Well met. Lord Tywin.

47
00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:06.765
It's Tyland.

48
00:05:08.558 --> 00:05:10.143
What sort of man are you?

49
00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:14.898
- I beg your pardon?
- A poet...

50
00:05:15.899 --> 00:05:17.067
a philosopher?

51
00:05:17.692 --> 00:05:20.320
I am the master of ships
at King's Landing.

52
00:05:20.904 --> 00:05:24.157
- You're thin.
- But also tall.

53
00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:30.163
I will not sail with a man
who cannot best me.

54
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.420
At what?

55
00:06:26.928 --> 00:06:28.888
Some rum wouldn't go amiss.

56
00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:31.641
Your Grace.

57
00:06:32.434 --> 00:06:34.060
Just a little.

58
00:06:42.652 --> 00:06:44.863
You're a good man. Orwyle.

59
00:06:57.542 --> 00:06:58.752
A word. Your Grace?

60
00:07:19.105 --> 00:07:21.941
I must ask you. Your Grace.
to steel yourself.

61
00:07:23.026 --> 00:07:27.530
We must leave King's Landing. quickly.
and we will not return for some time.

62
00:07:29.324 --> 00:07:30.324
What?

63
00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:33.786
The Pretender has found three
new riders for her dragons.

64
00:07:33.787 --> 00:07:37.248
- That's impossible.
- Your brother thought the same.

65
00:07:37.249 --> 00:07:40.126
He flew to challenge her and was rebuffed.

66
00:07:40.127 --> 00:07:42.170
Fled in terror. from what I hear.

67
00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:46.256
He deserves no less.

68
00:07:46.257 --> 00:07:50.595
Be that as it may.
he has gone in fury to Sharp Point

69
00:07:51.262 --> 00:07:53.890
and laid waste to the whole of the town.

70
00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:57.727
Fucking mad cunt.

71
00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:01.690
She really did it then?

72
00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:04.025
I fear so.

73
00:08:05.777 --> 00:08:08.571
So what was the fucking point
in all this then?

74
00:08:09.989 --> 00:08:15.704
The gods are cruel. Your Grace.
but I hope you can see the urgency.

75
00:08:15.705 --> 00:08:18.707
No. no. I am the king.

76
00:08:19.332 --> 00:08:20.792
Why must I run?

77
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:23.712
Because the prince regent
is going to kill you.

78
00:08:28.091 --> 00:08:32.679
You were in danger before.
and now. he is thwarted and he is angry.

79
00:08:32.680 --> 00:08:35.807
There is no telling what he will do
but we have an opportunity

80
00:08:35.808 --> 00:08:38.893
- while he is away...
- An opportunity to push him out.

81
00:08:39.686 --> 00:08:41.729
Take me to my throne

82
00:08:41.730 --> 00:08:45.025
and once he returns.
I shall take him prisoner.

83
00:08:45.984 --> 00:08:47.152
And what then?

84
00:08:49.029 --> 00:08:51.448
When Rhaenyra descends
on you with her seven dragons

85
00:08:51.449 --> 00:08:53.700
and you. without Vhagar. what then?

86
00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:09.424
I have. over the years. in anticipation
of little bumps in the road.

87
00:09:09.425 --> 00:09:12.093
moved the greater part
of Harrenhal's gold reserves

88
00:09:12.094 --> 00:09:14.179
to the Iron Bank in Braavos.

89
00:09:14.180 --> 00:09:16.805
We can live well

90
00:09:16.806 --> 00:09:20.268
and remain until what is coming
has passed.

91
00:09:23.021 --> 00:09:28.276
You want to take me to Essos
to live with the goatfuckers.

92
00:09:29.569 --> 00:09:31.571
It's best to live. I think.

93
00:09:31.905 --> 00:09:34.074
- However you do it.
- Is it?

94
00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:38.078
My dragon is dead.

95
00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:40.163
I am burnt

96
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:42.165
and disgusting

97
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:44.000
and alone.

98
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:46.628
And I'm a cripple.

99
00:09:50.423 --> 00:09:51.799
You are not alone.

100
00:09:51.800 --> 00:09:54.760
My cock is destroyed.
did they tell you that?

101
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:58.451
Yeah. It burst into flames
like a sausage on the spit.

102
00:09:58.452 --> 00:10:02.143
Do not despair. Your Grace.
There are better days ahead.

103
00:10:02.602 --> 00:10:05.062
Let your brother and the Pretender

104
00:10:05.063 --> 00:10:08.107
destroy themselves
in blood and bitterness.

105
00:10:08.108 --> 00:10:12.570
When they are spent. and their armies
in tatters. we will return

106
00:10:12.571 --> 00:10:15.948
and the people will rise up to meet us.

107
00:10:15.949 --> 00:10:19.827
I can't even piss without it
running down my leg.

108
00:10:19.828 --> 00:10:23.707
They will be tired of endless deprivation
and fear.

109
00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:27.752
They will hail the returning king

110
00:10:28.420 --> 00:10:31.131
his father's true heir.

111
00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:34.843
Aegon the Victorious

112
00:10:35.552 --> 00:10:37.554
risen from the ashes.

113
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:40.640
Aegon the Peacemaker.

114
00:10:43.685 --> 00:10:45.687
Aegon the Rebuilder.

115
00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:51.860
Aegon. the Realm's Delight.

116
00:11:39.657 --> 00:11:42.618
This is more like it.
Hugh. don't you think?

117
00:11:42.619 --> 00:11:44.913
We're meant to be at the training yards
learnin' the commands.

118
00:11:44.914 --> 00:11:46.580
Yeah. and I will go

119
00:11:46.581 --> 00:11:50.001
but surely they'd not deny me
my pleasure after so long.

120
00:11:50.002 --> 00:11:51.878
I may never eat fish again.

121
00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:55.173
What are you doing here?

122
00:11:55.799 --> 00:11:57.258
Remove your feet from the table.

123
00:11:57.259 --> 00:11:59.510
- I'd rather not.
- Ulf.

124
00:11:59.511 --> 00:12:02.200
It's not up to you. Ulf.

125
00:12:02.201 --> 00:12:04.891
Who's it up to then. boy?

126
00:12:05.392 --> 00:12:08.144
He is the prince. Ulf.
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.

127
00:12:09.187 --> 00:12:11.981
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon. Right here.

128
00:12:12.982 --> 00:12:14.526
Who'd have thought it?

129
00:12:14.527 --> 00:12:15.610
He lives here.

130
00:12:16.403 --> 00:12:17.862
I'll have an apology from you.

131
00:12:19.698 --> 00:12:21.115
The young prince!

132
00:12:21.116 --> 00:12:23.034
And look at that hair.

133
00:12:24.828 --> 00:12:26.496
As dark as they say.

134
00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:29.874
Let them tell us we don't have
Targaryen blood. eh?

135
00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:34.421
- My mother is the queen and...
- Dragonriders both.

136
00:12:34.422 --> 00:12:37.798
You and I. cut from the same cloth.

137
00:12:37.799 --> 00:12:40.885
It is a sacred inheritance of which
you know nothing.

138
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:43.429
Forgive him. my prince.

139
00:12:43.430 --> 00:12:45.724
He is not much used to the manners
of court.

140
00:12:46.433 --> 00:12:48.143
Or any manners at all. I'd say.

141
00:12:48.768 --> 00:12:50.937
Do you know what has happened
this last hour?

142
00:12:52.522 --> 00:12:56.026
The so-called prince regent
has burned Sharp Point down to its stones.

143
00:12:56.027 --> 00:12:59.738
Thousands of its folk dead or lost.
Its harbor in ashes.

144
00:13:01.031 --> 00:13:03.658
Will you prepare to face such an enemy?

145
00:13:05.243 --> 00:13:07.954
Or will you stay here
and make yourself easy?

146
00:13:08.079 --> 00:13:12.667
If you hinder our efforts
through sloth or unreadiness.

147
00:13:12.668 --> 00:13:14.001
I will see you hanged

148
00:13:14.002 --> 00:13:16.379
and your body fed to the dogs
in the street.

149
00:13:17.380 --> 00:13:20.342
I meant no disrespect. my prince.

150
00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:41.613
The new riders are a boon to us.
but now the deed is done.

151
00:13:41.614 --> 00:13:44.115
I cannot erase my doubts.

152
00:13:44.783 --> 00:13:46.367
We know little of who they are

153
00:13:46.368 --> 00:13:48.870
and what is the strength
of their character.

154
00:13:48.871 --> 00:13:51.373
Addam of Hull. at least. is known to you.

155
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:55.042
He's a shipwright in my employ

156
00:13:55.043 --> 00:13:58.004
and it is reported to me
that he is a man of integrity.

157
00:13:58.797 --> 00:14:03.051
I've had little to do with him.
to my regret.

158
00:14:03.843 --> 00:14:06.241
But the beasts have been claimed.

159
00:14:06.242 --> 00:14:08.640
You now have a great advantage.

160
00:14:08.641 --> 00:14:10.766
You must strike. quickly.

161
00:14:10.767 --> 00:14:12.936
while the prince regent
mulls his next action.

162
00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:17.607
I had hoped my advantage may be
in deterrence.

163
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:22.570
Vhagar has ever been our foremost threat.
and she is now overmatched.

164
00:14:22.571 --> 00:14:24.280
Vhagar is not his only dragon.

165
00:14:24.948 --> 00:14:27.534
The third brother is untested.
has never left Oldtown.

166
00:14:27.535 --> 00:14:29.619
and his dragon is younger than Vermax.

167
00:14:29.620 --> 00:14:31.287
But a dragon nonetheless.

168
00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:33.123
And you forget another.

169
00:14:34.916 --> 00:14:36.126
Helaena?

170
00:14:36.668 --> 00:14:38.962
She does not ride.
She has no taste for it.

171
00:14:38.963 --> 00:14:41.296
She may yet be compelled.

172
00:14:41.297 --> 00:14:43.382
- And her dragon...
- Dreamfyre.

173
00:14:43.383 --> 00:14:45.468
hatched when the Conqueror was king.

174
00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:47.804
She is formidable.

175
00:14:48.555 --> 00:14:50.682
Still. Helaena is no warrior.

176
00:14:53.935 --> 00:14:55.812
Aemond thought himself invincible.

177
00:14:56.563 --> 00:14:58.189
He has now discovered he is not.

178
00:14:59.024 --> 00:15:01.234
He'll be angry. desperate.

179
00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:06.322
He will not stop at burning Sharp Point.
and he will not be denied.

180
00:15:07.073 --> 00:15:08.408
You speak truly

181
00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:11.244
though I wish it was not so.

182
00:15:16.249 --> 00:15:17.542
How goes the <i>Sea Snake?</i>

183
00:15:19.252 --> 00:15:20.879
Better than new.

184
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:23.757
We'll rejoin the blockade on the morrow.

185
00:15:24.215 --> 00:15:27.427
Let our foes beware.
be they Lannister or Greyjoy.

186
00:15:29.054 --> 00:15:32.682
But my ship is no longer the <i>Sea Snake.</i>

187
00:15:33.141 --> 00:15:35.727
She was a testament to my own glory.

188
00:15:36.644 --> 00:15:38.646
I've given her a new name.

189
00:15:40.982 --> 00:15:43.193
<i>The Queen Who Never Was.</i>

190
00:15:45.695 --> 00:15:46.905
Corlys.

191
00:15:48.073 --> 00:15:49.699
I thank you.

192
00:15:53.995 --> 00:15:57.457
What I do now. I do for her.

193
00:16:00.251 --> 00:16:02.211
Your Grace. you are ready.

194
00:16:02.212 --> 00:16:05.173
You have six dragons under your banner.

195
00:16:05.840 --> 00:16:09.594
My ships sail at your command.
and my men serve you.

196
00:16:10.387 --> 00:16:13.890
But the Lannisters are marching.
and the Hightowers from Oldtown.

197
00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:21.648
You must crush this beast at its head
and before too many days have flown.

198
00:16:25.068 --> 00:16:27.111
There is. of course.

199
00:16:27.112 --> 00:16:29.823
another player that has yet
to be revealed.

200
00:16:32.575 --> 00:16:34.618
Ah. Your Grace. a word.

201
00:16:34.619 --> 00:16:38.081
It seems the sheep on our land
has been sold upriver.

202
00:16:38.082 --> 00:16:40.875
My vassals have sent a drove
of swine instead.

203
00:16:40.876 --> 00:16:42.668
Dragons do eat pigs. I assume?

204
00:16:42.669 --> 00:16:44.628
Caraxes prefers them.
How goes your muster?

205
00:16:44.629 --> 00:16:46.735
We'll be ready to march in two days' time.

206
00:16:46.736 --> 00:16:48.841
- See to those pigs.
- At once. Your Grace.

207
00:16:48.842 --> 00:16:52.637
Your Grace. Ser Alfred Broome
has come to see you.

208
00:16:54.055 --> 00:16:55.180
Interesting.

209
00:16:55.181 --> 00:16:57.182
I am sent as an emissary from the queen

210
00:16:57.183 --> 00:16:59.643
to ascertain your movements
and your intentions.

211
00:16:59.644 --> 00:17:03.523
You've arrived just in time
to see my new army. Broome.

212
00:17:03.524 --> 00:17:05.233
What do you think of it?

213
00:17:05.234 --> 00:17:07.027
It's very large.

214
00:17:09.320 --> 00:17:11.322
Lannister hesitates.

215
00:17:11.781 --> 00:17:14.492
I aim to march on King's Landing
before he can catch me.

216
00:17:14.493 --> 00:17:17.203
May I have a word in private. Your Grace?

217
00:17:21.875 --> 00:17:23.877
I would speak honestly with you.

218
00:17:23.878 --> 00:17:25.461
I'd expect nothing less.

219
00:17:25.462 --> 00:17:28.172
I was faithful to the king. your brother.

220
00:17:28.173 --> 00:17:30.883
I pledged my banners
to Rhaenyra. his heir.

221
00:17:30.884 --> 00:17:34.679
I will never serve the usurpers
or the whelps of Oldtown

222
00:17:34.680 --> 00:17:36.722
but there are battles to be fought...

223
00:17:36.723 --> 00:17:39.434
- Traitor.
- ...and in times like this...

224
00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:44.147
Did you hear something?

225
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:48.735
This place will have you barking
at the moon.

226
00:17:51.738 --> 00:17:55.158
While you have mustered an army.
Rhaenyra has faltered

227
00:17:55.159 --> 00:17:57.034
turning aside from our judgment

228
00:17:57.035 --> 00:17:59.370
and taking a course.
I myself. deem reckless.

229
00:17:59.371 --> 00:18:03.416
Rhaenyra will chart her own course.
for good or ill.

230
00:18:03.417 --> 00:18:05.377
But you are a leader of men.

231
00:18:06.795 --> 00:18:08.942
If you declare yourself.

232
00:18:08.943 --> 00:18:11.091
your lords will follow you.

233
00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:14.552
I never took you for a turncloak.

234
00:18:15.512 --> 00:18:17.138
Ser Alfred.

235
00:18:20.016 --> 00:18:22.227
Rhaenyra's intentions are good.

236
00:18:24.020 --> 00:18:27.649
But what we need. in this moment.

237
00:18:29.317 --> 00:18:30.735
is a king.

238
00:18:57.554 --> 00:18:59.263
<i>It appears that the Pretender</i>

239
00:18:59.264 --> 00:19:01.495
sent boats to collect
those among the smallfolk

240
00:19:01.496 --> 00:19:03.727
who believed they had any drop
of Targaryen blood.

241
00:19:03.728 --> 00:19:05.811
Deception and subterfuge.

242
00:19:05.812 --> 00:19:08.981
Cowards. all of them.
Put an end to this madness.

243
00:19:08.982 --> 00:19:12.277
Let no vessel come or go from our harbor
without our inspection.

244
00:19:12.278 --> 00:19:14.612
This will hinder the work
of the fishing boats.

245
00:19:14.613 --> 00:19:16.739
The people depend on them for sustenance.

246
00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:20.785
They will need no sustenance
if they are slaughtered by the enemy.

247
00:19:20.786 --> 00:19:23.079
We must all make our sacrifices.

248
00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:27.959
<i>Why does everybody hate us?</i>

249
00:19:27.960 --> 00:19:29.960
They're unhappy

250
00:19:29.961 --> 00:19:32.464
and unhappy people
look for someone to hate.

251
00:19:36.092 --> 00:19:38.052
We didn't order the blockade.

252
00:19:38.053 --> 00:19:41.222
No. but we are the crown
so they expect us to break it.

253
00:19:42.557 --> 00:19:43.767
Drink this.

254
00:19:50.982 --> 00:19:53.610
I was happier before I was queen.

255
00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:02.619
What would you think
about leaving this place?

256
00:20:11.419 --> 00:20:12.712
Where would I go?

257
00:20:19.761 --> 00:20:21.825
The prince regent. Your Grace.

258
00:20:21.826 --> 00:20:23.890
Helaena. Here you are. Mother.

259
00:20:26.768 --> 00:20:30.105
- I was just going to bed.
- The crown has need of your service.

260
00:20:30.230 --> 00:20:32.148
- Now?
- The Pretender has raised new riders

261
00:20:32.149 --> 00:20:35.402
against us. and we must answer in kind.

262
00:20:36.611 --> 00:20:38.405
I need you to fly
with Dreamfyre to battle.

263
00:20:38.406 --> 00:20:40.490
- Aemond.
- I do not wish to fight.

264
00:20:40.491 --> 00:20:42.574
Our wishes must take second place now

265
00:20:42.575 --> 00:20:45.286
to what is necessary
to preserve the throne.

266
00:20:46.162 --> 00:20:48.164
I won't burn anyone.

267
00:20:50.250 --> 00:20:51.625
It isn't a question.

268
00:20:51.626 --> 00:20:53.378
- Aemond.
- They have defiled our birthright.

269
00:20:53.379 --> 00:20:55.087
made commoners into dragonlords!

270
00:20:55.088 --> 00:20:56.649
- Aemond! Aemond!
- It is a sin and must be punished!

271
00:20:56.673 --> 00:20:58.424
May I remind you your sister
is still the queen?

272
00:20:58.425 --> 00:21:02.012
As you were once! And you see now
what is the consequence of your weakness!

273
00:21:02.013 --> 00:21:04.138
We are in peril today more than yesterday!

274
00:21:04.139 --> 00:21:06.766
Was it peril that moved you to burn
the town of Sharp Point?

275
00:21:06.767 --> 00:21:09.436
Peril or basest fury
at your own humiliation?

276
00:21:11.271 --> 00:21:12.646
You wish to rule the Seven Kingdoms.

277
00:21:12.647 --> 00:21:16.859
but you rain ruin and death upon
its smallfolk when you've been insulted

278
00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:21.072
because it makes you feel strong
and now you seek to corrupt your sister.

279
00:21:21.073 --> 00:21:22.970
of all our line.
the gentlest and most deserving

280
00:21:22.971 --> 00:21:24.868
- of your protection.
- And who will protect her

281
00:21:24.869 --> 00:21:26.118
if she cannot protect herself?

282
00:21:26.119 --> 00:21:27.912
And who will she be
if her mind is broken?

283
00:21:27.913 --> 00:21:29.706
'Tis no longer our rule
that is threatened.

284
00:21:29.707 --> 00:21:30.956
our very lives.

285
00:21:30.957 --> 00:21:32.877
- Would you not have us prevail?
- Not like this.

286
00:21:36.546 --> 00:21:38.381
Not like this!

287
00:21:55.315 --> 00:21:56.733
Your Grace.

288
00:21:57.525 --> 00:21:58.735
Grand Maester.

289
00:22:00.153 --> 00:22:02.364
I must again request your assistance.

290
00:22:03.114 --> 00:22:04.741
I need passage.

291
00:22:05.658 --> 00:22:07.452
And your discretion.

292
00:22:19.464 --> 00:22:22.300
Do you think nothing of your oath.

293
00:22:24.302 --> 00:22:25.720
Lord Commander?

294
00:22:27.889 --> 00:22:29.933
I think of nothing else. my lord.

295
00:22:31.351 --> 00:22:36.356
Steward's son from Dorne
fucking the queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

296
00:22:38.400 --> 00:22:40.026
Former queen.

297
00:22:40.985 --> 00:22:43.383
She has broken no oath.
for all I may have done.

298
00:22:43.384 --> 00:22:45.917
- I could send you to the Wall.
- You could.

299
00:22:45.918 --> 00:22:48.451
Stain the Hightower name for a generation.

300
00:22:49.327 --> 00:22:52.163
- King's mother and his Hand.
- She is my sister.

301
00:22:55.083 --> 00:22:56.876
She saved my life.

302
00:22:57.919 --> 00:22:59.336
Twice.

303
00:22:59.337 --> 00:23:02.090
Once from the headsman's axe
and once from myself.

304
00:23:05.802 --> 00:23:08.430
Since then. she has been
the beacon I follow.

305
00:23:18.064 --> 00:23:20.692
Do not think I have no shame in me. ser.

306
00:23:22.068 --> 00:23:24.821
Desire for women has brought me
grief after grief.

307
00:23:25.405 --> 00:23:26.740
Then resist it.

308
00:23:29.409 --> 00:23:31.118
Oh. would that it were so simple.

309
00:23:31.119 --> 00:23:33.913
Your brothers in the Kingsguard
find a way.

310
00:23:37.083 --> 00:23:38.460
Do they?

311
00:23:40.462 --> 00:23:41.838
Perhaps they do.

312
00:23:43.882 --> 00:23:46.301
Or perhaps all men are corrupt

313
00:23:48.053 --> 00:23:50.472
and true honor is a mist

314
00:23:51.389 --> 00:23:52.766
that melts in the morning.

315
00:23:55.477 --> 00:23:57.520
That is a bleak philosophy.

316
00:23:58.104 --> 00:23:59.939
I have no philosophy.

317
00:24:01.274 --> 00:24:03.485
Or rather. my philosophy was this.

318
00:24:05.904 --> 00:24:09.657
To protect the righteous
and dispense justice on the rest.

319
00:24:11.785 --> 00:24:12.994
But now.

320
00:24:16.331 --> 00:24:18.166
you saw what I saw.

321
00:24:23.463 --> 00:24:27.467
The dragons dance.
and men are like dust under their feet.

322
00:24:31.096 --> 00:24:34.557
And all our fine thoughts.
all our endeavors

323
00:24:34.558 --> 00:24:36.267
are as nothing.

324
00:24:42.148 --> 00:24:44.984
We march now toward our annihilation.

325
00:24:51.449 --> 00:24:53.910
To die will be a kind of relief.

326
00:24:58.581 --> 00:24:59.958
Don't you think?

327
00:26:39.641 --> 00:26:41.685
You have impressed me. Lord Tyman.

328
00:26:42.894 --> 00:26:46.314
King's Landing has sent a most
doughty ambassador.

329
00:26:49.484 --> 00:26:55.198
I hope you will testify to the worth
of the ambassador

330
00:26:55.199 --> 00:26:58.535
by agreeing to his most humble request.

331
00:26:59.035 --> 00:27:01.538
I will most certainly consider it.

332
00:27:09.462 --> 00:27:11.131
After dinner.

333
00:27:15.635 --> 00:27:18.221
Have you ever eaten
the flesh of your enemies?

334
00:27:19.055 --> 00:27:20.056
What?

335
00:27:22.267 --> 00:27:25.145
I have not and I would not.

336
00:27:26.938 --> 00:27:31.359
So you reject the hospitality of my house.

337
00:27:42.203 --> 00:27:43.496
A jest. my lord.

338
00:27:44.914 --> 00:27:47.751
What do you take me for?

339
00:27:50.795 --> 00:27:52.005
A jest!

340
00:27:53.048 --> 00:27:54.299
Come.

341
00:28:09.147 --> 00:28:11.566
It does not befit a prince to pout.

342
00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:14.943
I'm not pouting.

343
00:28:14.944 --> 00:28:16.404
What would you call it. then?

344
00:28:18.907 --> 00:28:22.118
- I'm reading.
- While your mother waits?

345
00:28:25.997 --> 00:28:27.624
You're angry.

346
00:28:30.835 --> 00:28:32.002
Aren't you?

347
00:28:32.003 --> 00:28:33.546
I don't see what good it would do.

348
00:28:34.839 --> 00:28:36.466
They are an insult to us.

349
00:28:37.425 --> 00:28:39.176
To what makes us Targaryens.

350
00:28:39.177 --> 00:28:41.095
If any common lout can ride a dragon.

351
00:28:41.096 --> 00:28:43.890
- then...
- That does not make me common. Or you.

352
00:28:45.433 --> 00:28:48.018
- You know what I am.
- I don't care.

353
00:28:48.019 --> 00:28:51.898
You are the crown prince.
the son of the rightful queen.

354
00:28:51.899 --> 00:28:53.440
and here you are sulking

355
00:28:53.441 --> 00:28:54.983
because you believe that
if not for the dragon

356
00:28:54.984 --> 00:28:58.196
or the trappings of your station.
that you are nothing.

357
00:28:59.280 --> 00:29:01.074
Do you believe that you
are the first noble heir

358
00:29:01.075 --> 00:29:03.368
who was not sired by his noble father?

359
00:29:04.119 --> 00:29:06.495
Such is the way of the world. Jace.

360
00:29:06.496 --> 00:29:09.582
and in resenting it.
you only diminish yourself.

361
00:29:09.583 --> 00:29:11.292
Easy enough to say.

362
00:29:11.793 --> 00:29:14.254
I've heard the whispers
the whole of my life.

363
00:29:14.255 --> 00:29:16.547
Then prove to them that you are worthy.

364
00:29:16.548 --> 00:29:19.592
Get up and take your place
by your mother's side.

365
00:30:12.771 --> 00:30:14.773
Well done. Lord Tyrod!

366
00:30:23.490 --> 00:30:26.326
Good song. well delivered.

367
00:30:29.454 --> 00:30:31.039
It's Tyland.

368
00:30:33.208 --> 00:30:36.168
You have proven yourself
most accommodating.

369
00:30:36.169 --> 00:30:39.422
And more accomplished
than one would think. to look at you.

370
00:30:40.757 --> 00:30:42.092
Well...

371
00:30:44.844 --> 00:30:48.056
I will be pleased to sail at your side.

372
00:30:49.933 --> 00:30:52.394
And my captains with me.

373
00:31:00.193 --> 00:31:02.987
To the Gullet on the morrow!

374
00:31:09.452 --> 00:31:14.124
And let the Sea Snake
rue the day we meet again.

375
00:31:18.545 --> 00:31:22.424
Ya! My king will be well pleased.
To friendship!

376
00:31:36.938 --> 00:31:38.356
It is late.

377
00:31:43.111 --> 00:31:44.738
Before you go.

378
00:31:45.447 --> 00:31:46.614
Lord Tyland.

379
00:31:49.242 --> 00:31:50.826
You are a handsome man.

380
00:31:50.827 --> 00:31:56.541
and you have proven
your worth and virility.

381
00:31:58.710 --> 00:32:00.712
I wish to have children by you.

382
00:32:05.133 --> 00:32:08.720
You... You want me to...

383
00:32:08.721 --> 00:32:10.013
Indeed.

384
00:32:12.682 --> 00:32:14.768
I want you to fuck my wives.

385
00:32:19.439 --> 00:32:22.650
How many wives do you have?

386
00:32:27.364 --> 00:32:28.990
More wine here!

387
00:32:30.742 --> 00:32:32.744
Taming a dragon is thirsty work.

388
00:32:37.749 --> 00:32:40.377
Oh. and some more of these little birds.

389
00:32:47.342 --> 00:32:48.760
A toast.

390
00:32:50.512 --> 00:32:52.722
To our new riders.

391
00:32:53.932 --> 00:32:56.225
The three of you are not of noble birth

392
00:32:56.226 --> 00:32:59.270
but you have done a thing
never dreamed of before now.

393
00:33:11.116 --> 00:33:14.639
I have entrusted you with a power
only few have known.

394
00:33:14.640 --> 00:33:18.164
And I charge you to take it up
with fealty and respect.

395
00:33:18.998 --> 00:33:22.002
Serve me well. and I will make you
knights of the realm.

396
00:33:24.295 --> 00:33:25.714
What do you think of that. boys?

397
00:33:26.297 --> 00:33:28.653
We'll be knights. just like that.

398
00:33:28.654 --> 00:33:31.011
We will not fail you. my queen.

399
00:33:32.846 --> 00:33:34.472
What must we do?

400
00:33:37.058 --> 00:33:40.061
I had thought the mere
fact of you might stay the enemy's hand.

401
00:33:41.980 --> 00:33:43.732
But Lord Corlys is right.

402
00:33:44.149 --> 00:33:47.360
We must strike while we have the advantage

403
00:33:48.028 --> 00:33:49.237
and end this war.

404
00:33:49.654 --> 00:33:52.282
Learn your beasts and your commands.

405
00:33:52.782 --> 00:33:54.409
You will fly in two days' time.

406
00:33:55.285 --> 00:33:58.872
The strongholds of the usurper.
Oldtown and Lannisport.

407
00:33:58.873 --> 00:34:02.584
and their armies. all must be subdued.

408
00:34:03.376 --> 00:34:06.171
Alone. without allies.
he will have no choice but to surrender.

409
00:34:06.172 --> 00:34:08.444
You wish for us to kill innocents.

410
00:34:08.445 --> 00:34:10.717
- And so many.
- It is hard...

411
00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:13.553
but it cannot be helped.

412
00:34:18.475 --> 00:34:20.560
We must break the will of our enemy

413
00:34:21.561 --> 00:34:24.356
or more will die in a struggle
that stretches on without end.

414
00:34:24.357 --> 00:34:25.899
What about Vhagar?

415
00:34:27.150 --> 00:34:31.780
She is fearsome. but she is one dragon.

416
00:34:33.156 --> 00:34:36.033
The prince regent cannot
defend against all of us.

417
00:34:36.034 --> 00:34:38.912
I'll take him on myself.
Silverwing's a goer. she is.

418
00:34:38.913 --> 00:34:40.538
We're afraid of nothing.

419
00:34:41.706 --> 00:34:44.084
- Even if you are.
- There will be time enough

420
00:34:44.085 --> 00:34:45.794
to see which one of us is a coward.

421
00:34:47.087 --> 00:34:49.422
I said more of these little birds!

422
00:34:51.174 --> 00:34:55.387
A knight will comport himself
with grace at the queen's table.

423
00:34:55.804 --> 00:34:57.138
Best make me a knight. then.

424
00:35:01.476 --> 00:35:03.311
You forget yourself.

425
00:35:04.938 --> 00:35:06.147
friend.

426
00:35:10.568 --> 00:35:12.570
A sense of humor would do you all good.

427
00:35:23.748 --> 00:35:26.835
There is a message from Harrenhal.
Your Grace.

428
00:35:33.299 --> 00:35:34.466
Daemon?

429
00:35:34.467 --> 00:35:37.387
The castellan. Ser Simon Strong.

430
00:35:37.804 --> 00:35:39.681
Daemon has raised his army

431
00:35:40.598 --> 00:35:43.018
but Ser Simon fears treachery.

432
00:35:46.896 --> 00:35:48.732
I will not allow it.

433
00:35:50.859 --> 00:35:51.860
Addam.

434
00:35:53.069 --> 00:35:54.279
come with me.

435
00:36:00.076 --> 00:36:01.286
{\an8}Thank you.

436
00:36:02.620 --> 00:36:03.621
{\an8}Birds.

437
00:36:25.310 --> 00:36:27.354
Do you never sleep. witch?

438
00:36:32.317 --> 00:36:34.402
I'm goin' to the godswood.

439
00:37:12.148 --> 00:37:15.151
When you came here.
you were a closed fist.

440
00:37:17.696 --> 00:37:21.324
You wished to bend the world to your will.

441
00:37:23.952 --> 00:37:29.290
But you've discovered. I think.
that this world will not be governed.

442
00:37:35.797 --> 00:37:39.217
There are omens here
for those who seek them.

443
00:37:42.679 --> 00:37:44.388
You do not scoff?

444
00:37:44.389 --> 00:37:46.433
I'm no longer inclined to.

445
00:37:49.102 --> 00:37:51.062
I'm pleased to hear it.

446
00:38:02.782 --> 00:38:06.286
Do you wish. then.
to learn what is given to you?

447
00:38:14.627 --> 00:38:18.298
All your life. you have sought
to command your own fate.

448
00:38:22.886 --> 00:38:25.055
But today you are ready.

449
00:39:48.596 --> 00:39:50.849
It's all a story

450
00:39:59.858 --> 00:40:02.485
and you are but one part in it.

451
00:40:04.404 --> 00:40:06.448
You know your part.

452
00:40:16.666 --> 00:40:19.085
<i>You know what you must do.</i>

453
00:40:27.719 --> 00:40:28.928
Sister.

454
00:40:29.679 --> 00:40:32.849
We share the same blood. you and I.

455
00:40:33.808 --> 00:40:36.644
I know you wish no harm to anyone.

456
00:40:38.938 --> 00:40:41.231
But in a time like this.

457
00:40:41.232 --> 00:40:43.943
when the good of the realm
depends on us...

458
00:40:47.030 --> 00:40:49.866
{\an8}Our mother is not a dragonrider.

459
00:40:50.367 --> 00:40:52.284
{\an8}She cannot understand

460
00:40:52.285 --> 00:40:55.372
that you and I have a truer call to heed.

461
00:41:00.126 --> 00:41:01.753
Come with me...

462
00:41:02.962 --> 00:41:04.381
to Harrenhal?

463
00:41:06.424 --> 00:41:09.427
We will lay waste to Daemon and his army.

464
00:41:10.261 --> 00:41:15.308
Let our enemy see that we will answer
outrage with outrage.

465
00:41:15.309 --> 00:41:17.394
And if I refuse?

466
00:41:20.355 --> 00:41:22.982
Will you burn me as you did Aegon?

467
00:41:27.028 --> 00:41:29.406
- That is a lie.
- I saw it.

468
00:41:33.368 --> 00:41:37.080
You burned him and you let him fall.

469
00:41:41.167 --> 00:41:43.169
What you say is treason.

470
00:41:45.588 --> 00:41:48.008
Aegon will be king again.

471
00:41:51.094 --> 00:41:53.513
He's yet to see victory.

472
00:41:54.597 --> 00:41:57.225
He sits on a wooden throne.

473
00:41:57.976 --> 00:41:59.394
And you...

474
00:42:03.898 --> 00:42:05.900
you'll be dead.

475
00:42:08.611 --> 00:42:13.199
You were swallowed up in the God's Eye.
and you were never seen again.

476
00:42:18.747 --> 00:42:21.249
I could have you killed.

477
00:42:22.250 --> 00:42:24.878
It wouldn't change anything.

478
00:43:45.500 --> 00:43:48.461
I am the castellan. Ser Simon Strong.
Your Grace.

479
00:43:48.462 --> 00:43:49.754
Well met.

480
00:43:50.755 --> 00:43:54.384
Welcome to Harrenhal. my queen.
I did not think to see you here yourself.

481
00:43:55.051 --> 00:43:57.428
Your message gave me much concern.

482
00:43:57.429 --> 00:43:59.889
Yes. I must admit I had reason to fear.

483
00:44:02.058 --> 00:44:03.435
But come. see for yourself.

484
00:45:33.983 --> 00:45:36.319
I wasn't expecting you.

485
00:45:38.905 --> 00:45:40.615
That seems rather a lapse in foresight.

486
00:45:44.369 --> 00:45:47.372
- I see you have done well here.
- They are sworn to me.

487
00:45:48.123 --> 00:45:50.166
And not a moment too soon.

488
00:45:55.130 --> 00:45:57.298
And to whom are you sworn?

489
00:46:54.981 --> 00:46:56.983
The realm's only hope

490
00:46:57.650 --> 00:47:01.821
is a leader who can unite it
and my brother chose

491
00:47:01.822 --> 00:47:02.906
you.

492
00:47:21.925 --> 00:47:24.094
You are the true queen. Rhaenyra.

493
00:47:25.178 --> 00:47:27.013
First of Her Name.

494
00:47:27.514 --> 00:47:29.516
Protector of the Realm.

495
00:47:30.183 --> 00:47:34.062
I am meant to serve you.
and all of these with me.

496
00:47:34.063 --> 00:47:36.021
until death

497
00:47:36.022 --> 00:47:38.525
or the end of our story.

498
00:48:28.158 --> 00:48:29.784
My queen.

499
00:48:39.794 --> 00:48:42.464
For every one of us who falls.

500
00:48:43.173 --> 00:48:44.674
a hundred of them!

501
00:48:45.467 --> 00:48:48.428
There will be no mercy!

502
00:48:48.928 --> 00:48:50.889
We fight for our queen!

503
00:49:36.559 --> 00:49:38.770
You sent for me. Lord Hand.

504
00:49:40.605 --> 00:49:42.816
Gulls are flying low today.

505
00:49:43.608 --> 00:49:45.318
The weather will change.

506
00:49:46.152 --> 00:49:48.654
Not until late. I think. but

507
00:49:48.655 --> 00:49:52.033
- I will ready the storm sails.
- We join the blockade.

508
00:49:52.034 --> 00:49:55.412
and are like to find ourselves in peril.
sooner than late.

509
00:49:56.538 --> 00:49:59.165
I wish to set out on good terms
with my first mate.

510
00:50:00.583 --> 00:50:02.292
Have I been remiss in my duties?

511
00:50:02.293 --> 00:50:05.005
You've done what is asked of you.
and more.

512
00:50:05.839 --> 00:50:12.053
But you are curt. silent.
and the men find you distant.

513
00:50:13.221 --> 00:50:15.682
You cannot lead if you do not inspire.

514
00:50:16.224 --> 00:50:18.852
Well. I never asked to lead.
as you well know.

515
00:50:21.688 --> 00:50:24.649
You have been given a position
to which all who serve here aspire.

516
00:50:27.277 --> 00:50:31.573
Forgive me. my lord.
I will endeavor to improve myself.

517
00:50:35.702 --> 00:50:38.121
I am trying to help you.

518
00:50:44.669 --> 00:50:46.046
You want to help me?

519
00:50:48.048 --> 00:50:50.216
Is this the help you offer after
all these years?

520
00:50:50.217 --> 00:50:52.594
A reminder to be grateful?

521
00:50:53.428 --> 00:50:54.721
I mean no offense.

522
00:50:55.638 --> 00:50:56.806
You may go.

523
00:51:00.518 --> 00:51:02.729
Do you know what it was like for us?

524
00:51:04.022 --> 00:51:06.190
To grow up fatherless.

525
00:51:06.191 --> 00:51:10.111
to be sneered upon as bastards.
never sure of the bread to feed us?

526
00:51:10.112 --> 00:51:12.572
Do you know what hunger does to a boy?

527
00:51:13.615 --> 00:51:15.241
What grief does?

528
00:51:15.950 --> 00:51:18.370
- Or shame?
- You are dismissed.

529
00:51:18.787 --> 00:51:23.708
I sold fish in the market
from cold dawn until sunset.

530
00:51:23.709 --> 00:51:26.502
putting by coppers
to stave off the winter.

531
00:51:26.503 --> 00:51:29.296
and I watched the man
who sired me walk past

532
00:51:29.297 --> 00:51:35.136
with his son and heir
with a fur around his shoulders.

533
00:51:35.804 --> 00:51:40.016
Choosing sweetmeats to eat
after supper by the fire.

534
00:51:42.936 --> 00:51:44.229
And now that boy is dead.

535
00:51:45.230 --> 00:51:47.189
And his sister before him.

536
00:51:47.190 --> 00:51:48.899
And the heir that took his place.

537
00:51:48.900 --> 00:51:52.612
And now. now. now you remember I live.

538
00:51:54.114 --> 00:51:56.115
Now you wish to...

539
00:51:56.116 --> 00:51:58.743
suddenly to scatter
the crumbs of your favor.

540
00:52:01.329 --> 00:52:05.291
I am an honorable man
and I will serve you because I must.

541
00:52:06.001 --> 00:52:12.757
But if it is all the same.
I will decline any offers of help.

542
00:52:15.468 --> 00:52:17.470
If I survive this war.

543
00:52:17.846 --> 00:52:20.265
I will continue as I began.

544
00:52:22.100 --> 00:52:23.309
alone.

545
00:53:14.611 --> 00:53:18.073
You have done what no one
else would dream of

546
00:53:18.074 --> 00:53:20.367
and you have been rewarded.

547
00:53:21.076 --> 00:53:23.328
The gods favor you.

548
00:53:24.245 --> 00:53:27.207
They put the means to victory
in your hands.

549
00:53:27.208 --> 00:53:31.418
And yet. to claim it. I must strike

550
00:53:31.419 --> 00:53:34.881
and in striking.
I doom thousands to their deaths.

551
00:53:39.803 --> 00:53:42.222
I do not believe my father
would've wished this.

552
00:53:43.098 --> 00:53:45.265
He left you with no choice.

553
00:53:45.266 --> 00:53:48.936
Be strong. You know you are just.

554
00:53:48.937 --> 00:53:53.483
You must not let the Realm fall to those
who care for power more than peace.

555
00:53:53.942 --> 00:53:56.111
You must prevail.

556
00:53:59.197 --> 00:54:01.199
And who pays the price?

557
00:54:19.217 --> 00:54:20.385
Come.

558
00:54:24.973 --> 00:54:26.975
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

559
00:54:40.405 --> 00:54:42.407
I had to see you.

560
00:54:51.249 --> 00:54:53.292
- Who knows?
- None save my protector.

561
00:54:53.293 --> 00:54:55.337
He laid down his sword at your gate.

562
00:55:05.096 --> 00:55:09.309
I've been. I think mistaken.

563
00:55:11.311 --> 00:55:12.520
In what?

564
00:55:13.605 --> 00:55:16.774
I was raised to believe
there was an order to things.

565
00:55:16.775 --> 00:55:21.071
that there was security
in following the paths laid out for us.

566
00:55:21.988 --> 00:55:25.408
I resented you. I think.
for caring so little for any of it.

567
00:55:25.409 --> 00:55:28.161
for knowing what you wanted.

568
00:55:28.703 --> 00:55:30.705
I did not know what I wanted.

569
00:55:31.247 --> 00:55:33.458
I knew only what was expected of me.

570
00:55:36.711 --> 00:55:39.881
- Why have you come here?
- Because I lost my way.

571
00:55:39.882 --> 00:55:42.592
Or rather. it was taken from me.

572
00:55:43.051 --> 00:55:47.806
All those I put my faith in. my husband.
my father. my lover. my son...

573
00:55:47.807 --> 00:55:51.393
The incorruptible queen
sullies herself with a lover.

574
00:55:51.394 --> 00:55:53.520
Do not judge me
for what you yourself have done.

575
00:55:54.187 --> 00:55:56.856
Your father died.
I took comfort with another.

576
00:55:57.482 --> 00:55:59.108
I too have desires.

577
00:55:59.109 --> 00:56:01.068
Yes. but you alone
made virtue your banner.

578
00:56:01.069 --> 00:56:06.908
And I clung to it. in defiance of you.
I think. who so disdained it.

579
00:56:17.836 --> 00:56:20.004
I have been alone. of late.

580
00:56:20.005 --> 00:56:24.467
I walked outside the walls of the city
and I felt a weight lifted from me.

581
00:56:24.801 --> 00:56:27.387
- How lovely for you.
- I thought. for the first time.

582
00:56:27.388 --> 00:56:29.472
what I would choose.

583
00:56:30.056 --> 00:56:31.891
if not for the duty I put before all else.

584
00:56:33.435 --> 00:56:35.957
Shall you cast your son down
and rule alone?

585
00:56:35.958 --> 00:56:38.481
No. I do not wish to rule. I wish to live.

586
00:56:39.065 --> 00:56:41.921
To be free of all this endless
plotting and striving.

587
00:56:41.922 --> 00:56:44.779
The crown will pursue war
and victory at any cost.

588
00:56:46.740 --> 00:56:48.074
But as for me.

589
00:56:49.784 --> 00:56:53.413
I would take my daughter
and her child and leave it all behind.

590
00:56:54.706 --> 00:56:58.335
It's too late. Alicent.

591
00:56:59.627 --> 00:57:00.669
You said it yourself.

592
00:57:00.670 --> 00:57:04.381
Blood has been shed.
cities burned. armies march.

593
00:57:04.382 --> 00:57:08.053
and you wish to wash your hands
of what you yourself set in motion.

594
00:57:08.054 --> 00:57:09.928
The arrogance of blaming me.

595
00:57:09.929 --> 00:57:11.722
as if you would not have been
challenged regardless.

596
00:57:11.723 --> 00:57:13.870
Did not your hand bring it forth
like a midwife?

597
00:57:13.871 --> 00:57:16.019
I did only what I thought
your father wanted.

598
00:57:18.229 --> 00:57:19.856
Oh. go then.

599
00:57:21.107 --> 00:57:22.484
Leave us behind. as you say.

600
00:57:22.485 --> 00:57:24.069
Rhaenyra.

601
00:57:24.861 --> 00:57:26.363
Wander in the wilderness.

602
00:57:27.405 --> 00:57:29.532
What has it got to do with me?

603
00:57:33.870 --> 00:57:36.873
Did you come here thinking
you would be absolved?

604
00:57:55.975 --> 00:57:58.603
He never stopped loving your mother.
you know?

605
00:57:59.312 --> 00:58:02.315
He was very fond of me. and I of him. but

606
00:58:03.274 --> 00:58:05.485
she was the vision that sustained him

607
00:58:06.403 --> 00:58:09.988
even after she herself
had slipped from his grasp. it was

608
00:58:09.989 --> 00:58:13.618
his love for her that kept him resolute
in his choice of heir.

609
00:58:13.619 --> 00:58:16.121
And yet. you believe
he wavered at the end.

610
00:58:22.544 --> 00:58:24.546
Why have you come here?

611
00:58:27.298 --> 00:58:30.301
Aemond will soon fly to join Cole
in the Riverlands.

612
00:58:32.679 --> 00:58:34.097
When he's gone.

613
00:58:34.681 --> 00:58:36.849
Helaena as queen will be
the crown's authority.

614
00:58:36.850 --> 00:58:39.060
If you come then to King's Landing.
I will see to it

615
00:58:39.061 --> 00:58:40.853
that our guards throw down their arms.

616
00:58:40.854 --> 00:58:43.940
we will open the gates.
we will shed no blood.

617
00:58:44.774 --> 00:58:46.151
You will enter as a conqueror.

618
00:58:48.653 --> 00:58:50.655
Already you have the stronger hand.

619
00:58:51.781 --> 00:58:53.158
Once you take the throne

620
00:58:54.576 --> 00:58:56.703
this senseless war must end.

621
00:58:59.330 --> 00:59:00.749
Right.

622
00:59:04.961 --> 00:59:06.171
What of Aegon?

623
00:59:13.553 --> 00:59:15.847
He's broken beyond recognition.

624
00:59:18.266 --> 00:59:21.269
He lies in the dark. in pain and terror.

625
00:59:21.770 --> 00:59:23.396
He has many faults. but

626
00:59:24.397 --> 00:59:27.025
he still heeds his mother.
I believe I can prevail upon him

627
00:59:27.026 --> 00:59:30.278
- to bend the knee. if indeed...
- No! Still.

628
00:59:30.279 --> 00:59:31.988
you defend him.

629
00:59:33.740 --> 00:59:37.035
Still you imagine you
can have all you want

630
00:59:37.036 --> 00:59:38.535
without paying too high a price.

631
00:59:38.536 --> 00:59:40.789
- a price I had no choice but to pay.
- What I want

632
00:59:40.790 --> 00:59:42.874
is to set things right.

633
00:59:44.918 --> 00:59:48.838
If I am to take the throne.
I must put an end to the opposition.

634
00:59:50.131 --> 00:59:51.508
I must take Aegon's head.

635
00:59:52.092 --> 00:59:55.136
And I have to do it for all to see.
You know this.

636
00:59:56.888 --> 00:59:59.599
However you may try to evade it.
you know this.

637
01:00:10.568 --> 01:00:11.778
Choose.

638
01:00:21.287 --> 01:00:24.082
Will you shrink from what
you set out to do?

639
01:00:24.083 --> 01:00:26.167
Or will you see it through

640
01:00:27.460 --> 01:00:29.045
and make your sacrifice?

641
01:00:34.217 --> 01:00:36.219
A son for a son.

642
01:01:29.397 --> 01:01:31.399
You are much changed.

643
01:01:32.400 --> 01:01:35.153
Let us be done with this. please.

644
01:01:37.489 --> 01:01:39.908
And what do I do with you now?

645
01:01:41.743 --> 01:01:45.372
You let me go. to do what I promised.

646
01:01:46.623 --> 01:01:48.833
And you fly to the Red Keep
in three days' time

647
01:01:48.834 --> 01:01:50.710
and you take your throne.

648
01:01:50.711 --> 01:01:52.587
Or you take me for a liar.

649
01:01:54.255 --> 01:01:58.175
I have neither weapon nor armor.
My life itself is forfeit.

650
01:01:58.176 --> 01:02:02.097
I cast myself on the mercy of a friend
who once loved me.

651
01:02:03.973 --> 01:02:05.600
History will paint you a villain.

652
01:02:09.938 --> 01:02:11.940
A cold queen.

653
01:02:14.526 --> 01:02:17.153
grasping for power. and then defeated.

654
01:02:17.821 --> 01:02:19.823
Let them think what they must.

655
01:02:22.367 --> 01:02:24.577
I am at last myself

656
01:02:25.495 --> 01:02:27.037
with no ambition greater than to walk

657
01:02:27.038 --> 01:02:30.125
where I please
and to breathe the open air.

658
01:02:32.711 --> 01:02:35.338
To die unremarked and unnoticed

659
01:02:36.965 --> 01:02:38.591
and be free.

660
01:02:42.345 --> 01:02:44.764
You speak as if from a distant dream.

661
01:02:45.724 --> 01:02:47.142
Come with me.

662
01:02:51.146 --> 01:02:55.150
My part is here. whether I will or no.

663
01:02:56.276 --> 01:02:58.903
It was decided for me long ago.

664
01:03:05.410 --> 01:03:07.245
Go.

665
01:03:08.305 --> 01:04:08.596
Do you want subtitles for any video?
